def bitwise_operations(x, y):
    result = []
    result.append(x & y)
    result.append(x | y)
    result.append(x ^ y)
    count_x = bin(x).count('1')
    count_y = bin(y).count('1')
    if count_x >= count_y:
        result.append('x has more set bits')
    elif count_y > count_x:
        result.append('y has more set bits')
    return result
